   POTUS -- Presidents of the United States

   On This Date In POTUS History
     * 1789 George Washington proclaimed the first Thanksgiving Day.
     * 1863 Following Washington, Abraham Lincoln issued a proclamation
       announcing the last Thursday in November as Thanksgiving Day.

